  "id": "ALAS2023-2026-1488",
  "title": "Amazon Linux 2023 - ALAS2023-2026-1488: Important priority package update for kernel6.12",
  "issued": {
    "date": "2026-03-16 09:00:00"
  },
  "updated": {
    "date": "2026-03-26 00:26:00"
  },
  "severity": "Important",
  "description": "Package updates are available for Amazon Linux 2023 that fix the following vulnerabilities:\nCVE-2026-23140:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nbpf, test_run: Subtract size of xdp_frame from allowed metadata size\n\nCVE-2026-23136:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nlibceph: reset sparse-read state in osd_fault()\n\nCVE-2026-23047:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nlibceph: make calc_target() set t-\u003epaused, not just clear it\n\nCVE-2026-22990:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nlibceph: replace overzealous BUG_ON in osdmap_apply_incremental()\n\nCVE-2026-22984:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nlibceph: prevent potential out-of-bounds reads in handle_auth_done()\n\nCVE-2025-40149:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ntls: Use __sk_dst_get() and dst_dev_rcu() in get_netdev_for_sock().\n",
